The 2022 chapter of our ongoing story exponentiated the theme of highs and lows that surround any group attempting to make music as a career. 

Those brief, glorious moments were higher than ever before; while the lows were devastating. We’ve celebrated with new music, we’ve dealt with loss, we’ve traveled further in the world than we ever had thought our music could take us. 

New friends expanded our horizons, old ones gave us their shoulders to lean on. For that we are so grateful, and we’ll bring those experiences with us the only direction we can move: forward.

Happy New Years, love you all,

-Pacific Dub

Happy second birthday to Million Pieces the album 💔💔💔

This is a special album to me. Early 2019 I was feeling pretty defeated and un inspired with music. I was ready to make the pivot full time into the business side of the industry and stop writing/performing. Fast forward to March, we all were the first to lose our jobs and the last to come back. The pandemic was brutal for so many, but the silver lining was the ability to take a breath and slow down. This album is 100% a product of that opportunity. Thank you to everyone who has listened and continues to listen. I couldn’t do it without you. Happy birthday MP - Colton

Life update for you guys - on Monday 7/31 our trailer was broken into and over $20k worth of gear was taken. Ironically this happened the same week that we were set to release our new single “It’s All Good” about looking on the bright side of life. After a few days of digging, we were able to track down some of our stuff to a local pawn shop. Everything in this photo was recovered and is back in our possession, along with the gear they were unable to get out of the trailer during the theft. We weren’t able to recover everything, but we’re stoked on what we got back. Can’t wait to rock some shows with you all ❤️
